ProcedureHelp.#cdata:
Syntax: PROC DISTANCE <options> ; 
    BY variables ; 
    COPY variables ; 
    FREQ variable ; 
    ID variable ; 
    VAR level(variables </ opt-list>) ; 
    WEIGHT variable ; 

The DISTANCE procedure computes various measures of distance, dissimilarity, or 
similarity between the observations (rows) of a SAS data set. These proximity 
measures are stored as a lower triangular matrix or a square matrix in an output 
data set (depending on the SHAPE= option) that can then be used as input to the 
CLUSTER, MDS, and MODECLUS procedures. The input data set might contain numeric 
or character variables, or both, depending on which proximity measure is used.

StatementHelp.#cdata:
Syntax: FREQ variable;

The frequency variable is used for either standardizing variables or assigning rank 
scores to the ordinal variables. It has no direct effect on computing the distances.

Syntax: ID variable ;

The ID statement specifies a single variable to be copied to the OUT= data set and used 
to generate names for the distance variables. The ID variable must be character.

Syntax: COPY variables ;

The COPY statement specifies a list of additional variables to be copied to the 
OUT= data set.
